"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823410","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>As set out in response to 121614, any necessary changes will be done in a cost-efficient way with expenditure being kept to a minimum.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-01-22T16:26:19.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823410/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823410/answer","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823410/answer/previousversion/35482","Biography information for Jake Berry","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-16","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 8 January 2018 to Question 121624, whether he has made an estimate of the potential cost to the public purse of the renaming of his Department.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","122890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823411","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>It is our priority to ensure that the Move On Fund meets the needs of those who are homeless and victims of domestic abuse. As such the Department is taking time to tailor the design of the programme to work for the rest of England.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-01-23T13:01:21.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823411/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823411/answer","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823411/answer/previousversion/35486","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-16","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 5 January 2018 to Question 118353, for what reasons the homelessness funding announced in Budget 2016 is not being made available until 2018-19 in parts of England outside London.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","122891"
