"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823605","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-24","<p>The CEK joint venture has provided HS2 Ltd with assurances that in the event any member of the group being unable to deliver on its responsibilities, the remaining members, now Eiffage and Kier, would fill the gap.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-01-24T12:28:44.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823605/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823605/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-16","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the financial effect on the High Speed Two project of Carillion entering liquidation; and if he will publish that assessment.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Dame Cheryl Gillan","123066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823606","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-23","<p>This Government is committed to maintaining the overall size of the Armed Forces.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","123069","2018-01-23T11:41:56.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823606/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823606/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-16","Armed Forces: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to his oral contribution of 15 January 2018, Official Report, column.613, at what number the Government has made a clear commitment to maintaining personnel in the Armed Forces.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","123067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823607","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-24","<p>The Treasury has no made no such assessments. The decision to open and close branches remains a commercial judgement for banks. However, the impact of closures on communities must be understood, considered and mitigated where possible.</p><p> </p><p>The industry’s Access to Banking Standard, launched in May 2017, commits banks to ensure personal and business customers are better informed about branch closures and the reasons for them closing, along with the options they have locally to continue to access banking services, including specialist assistance for customers who need more help. The Access to Banking Standard is monitored and enforced by the independent Lending Standards Board.</p><p> </p><p>99% of personal and 95% of banks’ business customers are now able to withdraw cash, deposit cash and cheques, and make balance enquiries at a Post Office counter via its network of 11,600 branches. At Autumn Budget 2017, my predecessor wrote to the Post Office and UK Finance to ask them to raise public awareness of the banking services available at the Post Office for individuals and SMEs. I look forward to receiving their proposals later this month.</p><p> </p><p>More widely, the Government remains committed to supporting SMEs’ access to the finance they need to grow and expand, and has: established the British Business Bank to make finance markets work better for small businesses; supported challenger banks; introduced a bespoke regime for peer-to-peer lending; and made structural interventions such as the Bank Referral Scheme and the SME credit data sharing scheme.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","123070","2018-01-24T13:38:00.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823607/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823607/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-16","Small Businesses: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the relationship between the availability of bank branches and the numbers of loans issued to small and medium sized enterprises.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","123068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823608","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-23","<p>This Government is committed to maintaining the overall size of the Armed Forces.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","123067","2018-01-23T11:41:56.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823608/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823608/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-16","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to his oral contribution of 15 January 2018, Official Report, column.614 whether his Department plans to maintain the Armed Forces at the size they were at the 2017 General Election; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","123069"
