"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822838","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-18","<p>Jobcentre Plus work coaches undertake a thorough and comprehensive mandatory training programme. This programme includes a module about ‘Alternative Payment Arrangements’ and the role of work coaches in identifying claimant needs.</p><p>Work coaches learn about the importance of discussing ‘Personal Budgeting Support’ and financial health with claimants, and which Alternative Payment Arrangements are available for claimants who need additional help. This training helps work coaches to understand when an Alternative Payment Arrangement, such as Split Payments should be considered, and explains how to arrange for Alternative Payment Arrangements to be implemented.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-01-18T14:48:35.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822838/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822838/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-15","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what guidance is issued to jobcentre staff on handling requests to split universal credit payments between members of a household.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","122521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822839","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-18","<p>The Task and Finish group on Taxi and Private Hire Vehicles was established by the then Minister of State for Transport, John Hayes, and has received submissions from a number of disability representation organisations. I look forward to receiving the group’s findings soon.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-01-18T15:52:31.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822839/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822839/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-15","Taxis: Disabled","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that disabled people are represented on the working group on taxi and private hire vehicle licensing.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","122522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822840","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-19","<p>The questionnaire for the 2018 Civil Service People Survey is not yet finalised. Proposals for changes to the questionnaire will be considered in consultation with relevant stakeholders and building on the available evidence. Presenteeism is one area being actively considered.</p><p> </p><p>Limited changes are made to the questionnaire over time to maintain a useful time series and to keep the survey at a manageable length. Changes that have been made are outlined each year, when results are published, at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/civil-service-people-surveys#annual-results-across-the-civil-service</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-01-19T13:38:09.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822840/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822840/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-15","Civil Servants: Surveys","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 12 January 2018 to Question 121212, what changes the Government plans to make to the Civil Service People Survey in order to measure the extent of presenteeism.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","122523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822841","Home Office","false","2018-01-18","<p>We have noted the ruling of the UK Supreme Court in favour of the Scottish Government. Minimum unit pricing will continue to remain under review pending the impact of its implementation in Scotland.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-01-18T16:53:28.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822841/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822841/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-15","Alcoholic Drinks: Minimum Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the potential effect of a minimum unit price for alcohol in England on rates of alcohol-related crime.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","122524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822842","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-18","<p>Public Health England published an evidence review on the public health impact of alcohol and the effectiveness of policies for reducing alcohol-related harm in December 2016. The review concluded that reducing the affordability of alcohol is the most effective way of reducing alcohol harm, including hospital admissions and deaths, and targeted pricing measures are particularly effective at reducing harm in those groups most at risk.</p><p> </p><p>The review also found that targeting price increases at the cheapest alcohol is very effective and cost-effective and is able to substantially reduce harm in heavy drinkers without affecting moderate drinkers or the price of alcohol sold in pubs and bars. Modelling studies by the University of Sheffield on the impact of minimum unit price was shown to have a positive impact in closing the health inequalities gap between those in the highest and those in the lowest socioeconomic groups. These studies are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/polopoly_fs/1.661445!/file/Final_mup_iba_report.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/polopoly_fs/1.661445!/file/Final_mup_iba_report.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>Minimum unit pricing and its effects will continue to remain under review pending the impact of its implementation in Scotland.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-01-18T16:46:23.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822842/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822842/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-15","Alcoholic Drinks: Minimum Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of minimum unit pricing on alcohol-related hospital admissions.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","122525"
